commit.message: Update changelogs and bump the version number to 0.2

Merge pull request #3 from tomaszg7/master

Get rid of cpufreqnextgovernor script and do its work in cpupower.c.
Make the plugin compatible with recent kernels/cpupower, because
cpufreq_cpu_exists has been removed from the kernel 4.7.

Change the function to determine number of cpus

Starting from kernel 4.7 the function cpufreq_cpu_exists() is removed in favor of cpupower_is_cpu_online() which needs additional header cpuidle.h. Instead of using that, test the existence just by calling cpufreq_get_freq_kernel(): https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/tools/power/cpupower/lib?id=ac5a181
[a-z] in sudoers file might be locale-sensitive, replace with named class
Correct missing sudoers entry
Get rid of cpufreqnextgovernor script and do its work in cpupower.c

Merge branch 'Polynomial-C-master'

Bumped the version to 0.1.6-r1.
Some grammar and spelling was also corrected.

Bumped ebuild to EAPI-6. Quoting and whitespace fixes.

Use the makefile to install sudo config and emit an elog message that
instructs how to give users permission to change gouvernor/CPU settings.

Signed-off-by: Lars Wendler <polynomial-c@gentoo.org>
